30/03/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul said on Tuesday (29 March) that the government has sent a letter to the European Commission confirming its agreement to seal an enlarged customs union protocol with the EU, including Cyprus. 
He said the letter marks the formal beginning of the process. 
EU Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn confirmed receipt of the letter in Brussels and praised Turkey for demonstrating its desire to fulfil commitments made to the EU. 
Ankara has pledged to seal the customs deal by 3 October, when it expects to start membership talks with the Union. 
(NTV, TurkishPress.com, Bloomberg - 29/03/05)
